Palpatine can hop on a shuttle and reach pretty much anywhere in the galaxy within a couple of weeks. When a ship enters hyperspace with a proper calculation it is almost certainly going to exit where it wants in a timely fashion. It doesn't risk getting caught in a warp storm, get infiltrated by daemons, or flung through time.
This combines to result in an empire that is far more centrally planned and ruled, as opposed to the quasi-feudal system that the Imperium has, where most worlds are by necessity more or less completely autonomous.

Your nose contains cells called Olfactory receptors. There are about 1000 different kinds of them, though you probably don't have all of them. When a scent molecule comes into your nose, it tends to stick to some, but not to others. When a scent molecule sticks to an Olfactory receptor it sends a signal to your a specific area of your brain called the Olfactory Bulb. From there it sees which kinds of receptors are firing and how many are firing and figures out what smell it is and how strong. For example, these kinds of receptors are firing, these aren't, not alot of them are firing so this smells faintly of strawberries.
